<font color="#FF0000">PART II, AS REQUESTED.</font><br>
<tt>Thu May 15 20:42:54 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
PART II: My 18 year old son just got another solicitation from the Marines. He is about to graduate High School. They have been promising him this &quot;cool compass&quot; for at least 5 letters, and now, want to send out a recruiter to talk to him and his family about joining.  Of course I want to choke, or gag, not sure of which. He is getting as many of these from the military as he is from the 100's of colleges that think either he is smart or I am rich (neither I guess).  <br><br>
He asked me what I thought, and what had changed since &quot;my time&quot;. I said (1) never trust the government, it will rip you off every chance it can, (2) never join any branch of the military (a family tradition of sorts), cause you up the odds you will get killed, (3) keep your grades up, don't take drugs, and don't use me as a role model totally.  Partially is ok.  I realize that alot of the places I have been I would not go back to today, but then, there was no choice, and it felt right back then.  To risk one's life to stop others from going to Nam (&quot;risk&quot; is questionable in hindsight-but it was real then), was the right thing to do. Tom Dier has the right thinking on this and I like his grip. <br><br>
My wife's cousin, who reads this site, was the runner up for Surgeon General, former Senior Medical Officer on the U.S. Constellation Aircraft Carrier, and has a resume' as long as both my arms and legs, yet we carefully dance around each other about the Nam issue. Most of my relatives are in Fire, i.e. fire chiefs and firemen, and a few plumbers. <br><br>
My core beliefs have not changed. I trust not my government. Doc Del holds me out as some lab display, i.e. &quot;look, this guy has really changed&quot;. No Offense in that DocDel, but yes, I have.  AND I AM DAMN GLAD OF IT. I now have persons and electronic personalitys to hang on the stories of horror, I have had to re think and re examine my &quot;lazy&quot; thoughts, some were filled with dry rot and I dumped them. Some are re affirmed.  I will never trust the &quot;system&quot;, I will never allow my children to be ground up in the gears of the military. And I will never again allow myself to be seduced into thinking a few people represent an entire race.  I may be selective in who I want to hang out with, and realist about some views in America (i.e. Black on White Racism), but I don't just broad stroke it anymore.<br><br>
P.S., before any of you think I am some pacifist type, I shoot normally 22 or 23 on the Trap line of 25, and I love my Mini 14 with its 30 round clips as much as I did my old 56 chevy. Labels don't work. Sorry DocDel. I was a liberal. Now, I don't know. Pro Choice, anti-war, (but I realize some wars are necessary and required-i.e. nuking Saddam was ok with me), Government is too big and not to be trusted, but the Militia movement ain't me.  What am I?  Damn if I know. Just another bozo on the bus  I guess, but all of you have been incredible in helping me intro-spect.  Isn't this what group therapy is SUPPOSED to be all about.  Man, if this is the first real group therapy of cyberspace, the future will be ok. Trust me.<br><br>
Doc Spatz
